Before registration and after registration.

A. Before Registration (Pre-Registry Stage) ::::

Step 1: Token / Booking Amount--
Amount: ~1â€“5% of sale value
Mode: NEFT / RTGS / Cheque
Purpose: Locks the deal
Document: Receipt + Agreement to Sell

Step 2: Due Diligence--
Verify:Allotment letter, Sale deed chain, EC (latest), Mutation (sellerâ€™s name), NOCs, freehold, layout, conversion
No major payment at this stage

Step 3: Pre-Registry Balance Preparation--
Buyer arranges:Remaining sale amount, Stamp duty, Registration charges
Mode : RTGS / DD / Bankerâ€™s Cheque


B. At Registration (Registry Day â€“ MOST IMPORTANT) ::::


Step 4: Execution of Sale Deed--
Buyer & seller sign sale deed at Sub-Registrar office

Step 5: Final Payment--
Entire remaining sale amount is paid NOW
Mode: RTGS / Bankerâ€™s Cheque / Demand Draft
Payment is made after signing but before biometric/registration completion

Step 6: Registration Completed--
Biometric verification
Sale deed is registered
Buyer becomes legal owner


C. After Registration (Post-Registry Stage) ::::

Step 7: Possession Handover--
Seller hands over: Physical possession, Original documents, Possession letter (if applicable)

Step 8: Mutation & Tax Transfer--
Buyer applies for: Mutation in revenue records, Property tax transfer


Golden Rule (Very Important)

âŒ Never pay full amount before registry
âœ… Always pay bulk / final amount at registrar office on registry day
âœ… Use traceable banking channels only

